snippet.title: Whales stranded off Fraser Island
snippet.content: RANGERS are working frantically to comfort two beached whales stuck between Fraser Island and the mainland. Queensland Parks and Wildlife Service rangers were heading to a nearby island to undertake a planned burn when they spotted the two live whales on Sheridan Flats southwest of Ungowa around 9.30am this morning. The department said the 10 and 12m humpbacks were stranded in a similar spot to where a pod of killer whales were successfully freed in 2013. Rangers are currently waiting for high tide hoping the whales will refloat.
